<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-03T09:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-01T14:07:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3566: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-01-03T09:40:00-05:00" notBefore="1919-01-02T00:00:00+04:53"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received January 3, 1919, 9:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at]
                            Omsk.</p>
                        <p>“2. 2d. Foreign Office here states that it has received telegram from
                            former Minister for Foreign Affairs Sazonoff that <persName corresp="#p_DGAI">Denikin</persName> has recognized the <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> government. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>